msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Project-Id-Version: Yakuza 6 Translation\n"
"Last-Translator: SavT\n"
"MIME-Version: 1.0\n"
"Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8\n"
"Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit\n"
"Language: it\n"

msgctxt "0||||4"
msgid "Come on, Mom! You said you'd\r\nbuy me whatever I wanted!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "1||||4"
msgid "No means no, Ayaka! Let's go find\r\nsomething else for you, okay?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2||||4"
msgid "I don't want anything else!\r\nI already told you, I want Haruka-chan stuff!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3||||4"
msgid "Did she just say Haruka?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4||||4"
msgid "I know that's what you want, but no stores are\r\ngoing to keep her merchandise in stock these days."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5||||4"
msgid "L-Let's keep looking, then!\r\nHaruka-chan's the only one I want!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6||||4"
msgid "Even if we find a place, I'm not buying anything\r\nof hers for you. Her father is a very bad man, you know."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7||||4"
msgid "The daughter of such a terrible person must be\r\nterrible, too. There must be someone better out there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9||||4"
msgid "Mama, have you ever met Haruka-chan's dad?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10||||4"
msgid "Huh? O-Of course I haven't."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11||||4"
msgid "So you're just gonna decide he's bad\r\nbefore you even know what he's like?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12||||4"
msgid "Maybe he's really a good guy!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13||||4"
msgid "L-Look, my answer is final!\r\nI said no, so stop questioning me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14||||4"
msgid "That girl is a bad apple!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15||||4"
msgid "Seriously. There's no way someone raised\r\nby a yakuza could turn out okay."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16||||4"
msgid "So, that girl's a Haruka fan..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17||||4"
msgid "Hey, you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18||||4"
msgid "Huh? Wh-What do you want?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19||||4"
msgid "Are you a Haruka fan?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20||||4"
msgid "Y-Yeah, I am."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21||||4"
msgid "Oh! Do you like her too, Mister?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22||||4"
msgid "Hm? W-Well, yeah.\r\nI, um... I've always supported Haruka-chan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23||||4"
msgid "Really? I didn't know there were adults\r\nout there who like her! You're weird, Mister!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24||||4"
msgid "......"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25||||4"
msgid "Hey, Mister. Do you know anywhere\r\nI can buy some Haruka-chan stuff?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26||||4"
msgid "They used to sell it everywhere,\r\nbut now it's gone from all the stores."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27||||4"
msgid "Sorry, I'm not really sure."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28||||4"
msgid "Oh... Maybe they got rid of\r\nit all 'cause her dad is a yakuza."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30||||4"
msgid "I dunno what a yakuza is, but my mom says\r\nit means Haruka-chan's dad is a really bad man."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31||||4"
msgid "Oh, and she thinks that means his\r\ndaughter has gotta be bad, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32||||4"
msgid "I'm not even allowed to listen to\r\nHaruka-chan's music anymore."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33||||4"
msgid "I see. I'm sorry to hear that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34||||4"
msgid "By the way, when exactly did you\r\nstart liking Haruka-chan?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35||||4"
msgid "Um, it was a long time ago! Back when I lived in\r\nOsaka, I went to one of her handshake events."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36||||4"
msgid "My family's always moving 'cause of my dad's job,\r\nso it's been hard for me to make friends at school."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37||||4"
msgid "That changed at that event, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38||||4"
msgid "When I was there, I asked Haruka-chan\r\nwhat I can do to make more friends."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39||||4"
msgid "And? What did she say?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40||||4"
msgid "\"I'm not that good at making friends either,\r\nbut you can do it if you just keep smiling.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41||||4"
msgid "\"Let's smile together!\"\r\nThat's what she told me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42||||4"
msgid "Haruka really said that?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43||||4"
msgid "Yup! And once I did what she said and\r\nsmiled a lot, I made tons of friends at school!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44||||4"
msgid "That's why I'm Haruka-chan's biggest fan!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45||||4"
msgid "I see. I'm glad you asked her advice."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46||||4"
msgid "Me too!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48||||4"
msgid "What's your favorite thing about Haruka-chan, Mister?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49||||4"
msgid "How kind she is."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50||||4"
msgid "How kind she is...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51||||4"
msgid "Yeah. She always puts others first,\r\neven before her own needs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52||||4"
msgid "That's her greatest strength, without a doubt."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53||||4"
msgid "Oh, I totally get what you mean!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54||||4"
msgid "Even after that handshake event was over, I stayed\r\nbehind in the park so I could watch her some more."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55||||4"
msgid "Haruka-chan didn't sit by and let everyone else\r\nclean up, though. She joined in right away!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56||||4"
msgid "When I saw that, I knew she wasn't just cute.\r\nShe was super cool, too!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57||||4"
msgid "Not surprising. That sounds just like her."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58||||4"
msgid "Huh? Why do you have that\r\nbig smile on your face, Mister?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59||||4"
msgid "D-Do I?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60||||4"
msgid "You're so weird!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61||||4"
msgid "Her voice."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62||||4"
msgid "To be honest, it's saved me many times."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63||||4"
msgid "I agree! Hearing her sing always pumps me up!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64||||4"
msgid "Four years ago, as I was about to draw my last breath,\r\nher voice is what woke me up to reality."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "65||||4"
msgid "Huh? Whaddya mean?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "66||||4"
msgid "O-Oh, uh, I mean I've been using\r\none of her songs as my alarm clock since then."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "67||||4"
msgid "Really!? Haruka-chan's songs are what\r\nwake me up in the morning, too!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "68||||4"
msgid "H-Huh. What a coincidence."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "69||||4"
msgid "Her face."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "70||||4"
msgid "Yeah! Isn't she so totally cute?\r\nI love how Haruka-chan looks when she smiles!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "71||||4"
msgid "I agree."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "72||||4"
msgid "When I first met her, she was just a cheeky little brat,\r\nbut somewhere along the way, she started smiling."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "73||||4"
msgid "When you first met her...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "74||||4"
msgid "Yeah, a-about that. It must have been\r\na bit before her stage debut."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "75||||4"
msgid "Oh, really? Haruka-chan was probably\r\nsuper nervous about all sorts of stuff back then."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "76||||4"
msgid "Probably, yeah."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "77||||4"
msgid "She was always so cute during performances, though.\r\nEven if she was nervous, she'd smile straight through."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "78||||4"
msgid "I'm so bad at hiding how I feel.\r\nI wish I could be like her..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "79||||4"
msgid "No, I think being genuine is important, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "80||||4"
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "81||||4"
msgid "Haruka tends to keep her real emotions hidden away.\r\nThat's how she can act so strong and confident on stage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "82||||4"
msgid "I took that strength for granted, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "83||||4"
msgid "Hm...? What do you mean, Mister?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "84||||4"
msgid "Uh, never mind. It's nothing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "85||||4"
msgid "What I want to say is,\r\nit's not a bad thing to express how you feel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "86||||4"
msgid "If you're sad, you should cry. If you're happy, you\r\nshould smile like Haruka does. There's no shame in that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "87||||4"
msgid "Huh...? Okay."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "88||||4"
msgid "I'm so happy I get to talk about Haruka-chan!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "89||||4"
msgid "Me too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "90||||4"
msgid "I always used to see her on TV,\r\nor talk to people about her at school..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "91||||4"
msgid "...but everyone changed their minds after that concert."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "92||||4"
msgid "That's when my mom started saying Haruka-chan was\r\nraised by a bad man and I should support someone else."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "93||||4"
msgid "Right..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "94||||4"
msgid "Even so, I wanna keep cheering for her\r\nafter all the help she gave me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "95||||4"
msgid "She might not be an idol anymore,\r\nbut that doesn't mean I don't love her!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "96||||4"
msgid "That's good to hear."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "97||||4"
msgid "I really wanted some Haruka-chan stuff, though.\r\nI asked for it for my birthday and everything."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "98||||4"
msgid "...Okay. I'll go find some Haruka merchandise for you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "99||||4"
msgid "Huh? You will, Mister?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "100||||4"
msgid "I will. It's your birthday, isn't it?\r\nThink of this as a present."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "101||||4"
msgid "You mean it!? Thank you so much, Mister!\r\nOh, and my name's Ayaka. What's yours?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "102||||4"
msgid "Kiryu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "103||||4"
msgid "That's your last name, right?\r\nI wanna know your first name!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "104||||4"
msgid "...It's Kazuma."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "105||||4"
msgid "Kazuma-san! I can't wait for all the\r\nHaruka-chan stuff you're gonna bring me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "106||||4"
msgid "All right, I'm going to get going now.\r\nWait for me here, okay?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "107||||4"
msgid "Yeah, I'll be here! Thanks, Mister Kazuma!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "108||||4"
msgid "Now then, where can I buy\r\nsome Haruka merchandise?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "109||||4"
msgid "Maybe I should check over at Don Quijote.\r\nThey sell practically everything there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "110||||4"
msgid "Welcome!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "111||||4"
msgid "Right, I'm supposed to be helping Ayaka look for\r\nHaruka merchandise. I should ask if they have any."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "112||||4"
msgid "I have a question for you. Do you sell any merchandise\r\nhere of the former idol Haruka Sawamura?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "113||||4"
msgid "Haruka Sawamura, right? Let me go check\r\nin the back. Please hold on a moment."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "114||||4"
msgid "Okay."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "115||||4"
msgid "I'm sorry to keep you waiting, sir."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "116||||4"
msgid "It looks like Haruka Sawamura merchandise has been\r\ndiscontinued nationwide. We don't have anything."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "117||||4"
msgid "Right, okay then.\r\nI'll try somewhere else. Thank you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "118||||4"
msgid "Um..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "119||||4"
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "120||||4"
msgid "You might find something at the Club SEGA\r\nover in Theater Square."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "121||||4"
msgid "I occasionally see people over there who exchange\r\nall sorts of idol merchandise with each other."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "122||||4"
msgid "Is that so? You really know your stuff."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "123||||4"
msgid "I spend most of my free time there.\r\nAnyway, I didn't mean to intrude."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "124||||4"
msgid "No, you were a big help. Thanks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "125||||4"
msgid "All right."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "126||||4"
msgid "Are those the idol fans that guy was telling me about?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "127||||4"
msgid "I should try talking to them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "128||||4"
msgid "Excuse me. Can I ask you a question?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "129||||4"
msgid "Huh? Whaddya want, old man?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "130||||4"
msgid "I'm trying to find merchandise for an idol named\r\nHaruka Sawamura. Know where I can get some?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "131||||4"
msgid "Sawamura? Who's that?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "132||||4"
msgid "I gotta admit, it does sound familiar.\r\nI'm not really into oldies, though."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "133||||4"
msgid "Pardon?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "134||||4"
msgid "The chart-topping Yukitty's the only idol\r\nworth caring about nowadays!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "135||||4"
msgid "Whoever the premiere idol is,\r\nI'll be there cheering her on!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "136||||4"
msgid "So, I don't know much about people\r\nfrom the past. Sorry sorry!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "137||||4"
msgid "It's all right..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "138||||4"
msgid "Excuse me. Can I ask you a question?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "139||||4"
msgid "Y-Yes! What is it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "140||||4"
msgid "I'm trying to find merchandise for an idol named\r\nHaruka Sawamura. Know where I can get some?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "141||||4"
msgid "Haruka Sawamura...? Sorry, but I'm\r\nnot too familiar with national idols."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "142||||4"
msgid "Hm? What do you mean?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "143||||4"
msgid "W-Well, I'm all about the small-time\r\nlocal beauties these days."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "144||||4"
msgid "I don't really care much for the idols who prance\r\naround on national TV like they're so hot. Nope."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "145||||4"
msgid "Providing support for the hardworking\r\nsmall-time idols of Japan is my life's goal!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "146||||4"
msgid "I even have a collection of photos for idols from\r\nHokkaido all the way down to Okinawa. Wanna see?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "147||||4"
msgid "M-Maybe later."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "148||||4"
msgid "Excuse me. Can I ask you a question?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "149||||4"
msgid "Hmph? What seems to be the matter?\r\nYou require something of me?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "150||||4"
msgid "I'm trying to find merchandise for an idol named\r\nHaruka Sawamura. Know where I can get some?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "151||||4"
msgid "Haruka Sawamura... The name eludes me.\r\nShe must be an idol of the modern day, yes?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "152||||4"
msgid "No, she actually retired three years ago.\r\nI don't think that's very recent."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "153||||4"
msgid "I beg to differ, good sir."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "154||||4"
msgid "Pardon?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "155||||4"
msgid "In my humble opinion, idols are better\r\nwhen aged like a fine wine."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "156||||4"
msgid "The current generation of stars all appear\r\nthe same to me. It is quite a disconcerting trend."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "157||||4"
msgid "O-Oh. Sorry, I guess I asked the wrong person.\r\nForget I mentioned it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "158||||4"
msgid "Halt!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "159||||4"
msgid "Why don't we let our ears bear witness to the glorious\r\nsongs of the 70s together? They are quite riveting!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "160||||4"
msgid "I'd rather not."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "161||||4"
msgid "Excuse me. Can I ask you a question?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "162||||4"
msgid "Sure. What is it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "163||||4"
msgid "I'm trying to find merchandise for an idol named\r\nHaruka Sawamura. Know where I can get some?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "164||||4"
msgid "Hold on, did I hear you say Haruka Sawamura?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "165||||4"
msgid "Y-Yeah. I need some merchandise of hers for<symbol=em_dash_with_outline>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "166||||4"
msgid "Brother!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "167||||4"
msgid "Wh-What?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "168||||4"
msgid "I still remember her enchanting rise to stardom!\r\nRetirement came far too soon for such a fair maiden!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "169||||4"
msgid "If you really are a fellow fan of Haruka Sawamura,\r\nthat means we're brothers in love!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "170||||4"
msgid "Y-Yeah, she's great.\r\nHaruka-san's songs really touched my heart."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "171||||4"
msgid "I'm building a collection of her merchandise, but it's\r\nbeen tough finding things. Do you have any leads?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "172||||4"
msgid "I seeeee."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "173||||4"
msgid "Due to Haruka-san's turbulent retirement, all her merch\r\nis off the shelves. It's really driven up the resale price."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "174||||4"
msgid "The amount of time that's passed since then\r\nhas made things even more difficult, too!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "175||||4"
msgid "So that's what happened."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "176||||4"
msgid "However, I just heard the other day about a store\r\nthat has a super-rare photo of Haruka-san in stock."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "177||||4"
msgid "I was about to head over and snag it for myself,\r\nbut I don't mind surrendering it to you this time."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "178||||4"
msgid "Are you sure!? Where is this store?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "179||||4"
msgid "Just one second. It's still possible that you're just\r\na lowly scalper hoping to score a sweet haul to sell later."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "180||||4"
msgid "To prove your honor, you'll have to\r\nanswer a simple Haruka-san question."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "181||||4"
msgid "If you get it right, I'll know you're truly my brother\r\nand tell you where the store is."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "182||||4"
msgid "Okay, let's do this."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "183||||4"
msgid "All right! It's question time!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "184||||4"
msgid "What is the name of the incredibly famous song\r\nHaruka-san sang in her first Princess League appearance?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "185||||4"
msgid "So Much More!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "187||||4"
msgid "That's correct!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "188||||4"
msgid "You really are a brother of mine!\r\nThough, that was pretty easy..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "189||||4"
msgid "Anyway, I'll tell you what I know."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "190||||4"
msgid "The photo of Haruka-san is waiting for you\r\nover at a pawn shop called Ebisu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "191||||4"
msgid "But remember, it's a collector's item.\r\nThere are probably others trying to get their hands on it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "192||||4"
msgid "I wish you the best of luck, brother!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "193||||4"
msgid "Right, it sounds like I should hurry.\r\nWell, thanks for everything."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "194||||4"
msgid "So Much Less!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "196||||4"
msgid "Hmmm! Close, but no cigar!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "197||||4"
msgid "What!? I could've sworn that was it..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "198||||4"
msgid "If you can't answer my question, you'll\r\nnever be my true brother. Try again!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "199||||4"
msgid "Please, No More!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "201||||4"
msgid "That's what I should be saying to you\r\nwith an answer like that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "202||||4"
msgid "What!? I got it wrong?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "203||||4"
msgid "If you can't answer my question, you'll never\r\nbe my true brother. Try again!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "204||||4"
msgid "Sorry, I got a little confused earlier.\r\nI'm ready now, though. Give me the question."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "205||||4"
msgid "Hey, I have something to ask you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "206||||4"
msgid "Yes, what is it, sir?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "207||||4"
msgid "I heard you guys had a rare photo of\r\nHaruka Sawamura here. Do you still have it in stock?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "208||||4"
msgid "Well, we did get one in recently,\r\nbut I actually sold it moments ago."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "209||||4"
msgid "What!? A-All right then. Thank you..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "210||||4"
msgid "I look forward to your next visit, sir."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "211||||4"
msgid "Wh-What are you guys doing!? Give it back!\r\nKeep your filthy hands off my Haruka-chan!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "212||||4"
msgid "What the...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "213||||4"
msgid "What're you whinin' over this\r\nlittle scrap of trash for, huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "214||||4"
msgid "Hey, nerd! How 'bout you give us So Much More of yer\r\nmoney instead of buyin' this crap? You got more, yeah?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "215||||4"
msgid "G-Give it back!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "216||||4"
msgid "That's enough outta you.\r\nJust hurry up and give us your wallet!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "217||||4"
msgid "Hold on a second."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "218||||4"
msgid "The hell do you want?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "219||||4"
msgid "You there."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "220||||4"
msgid "Huh? Y-You mean me?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "221||||4"
msgid "Yeah, that's right.\r\nAre you a fan of Haruka Sawamura?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "222||||4"
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "223||||4"
msgid "What?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "224||||4"
msgid "The hell's this bitch sayin'?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "225||||4"
msgid "What's your answer?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "226||||4"
msgid "Y-Yes, I'm a huge fan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "227||||4"
msgid "All right, then."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "228||||4"
msgid "What's all this about, gramps?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "229||||4"
msgid "You punks just ran out of luck.\r\nI can't let you abuse a Haruka fan like this."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "230||||4"
msgid "Huh? You trippin', man?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "231||||4"
msgid "Whatever. C'mon, we're just gonna have\r\nto take both of their wallets instead!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "233||||4"
msgid "The hell's up with this nerd?\r\nWhy's he so strong!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "234||||4"
msgid "Hey, are you okay?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "235||||4"
msgid "Y-Yes! Thank you so much for helping me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "236||||4"
msgid "Here. I got your picture back for you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "237||||4"
msgid "Oh, actually..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "238||||4"
msgid "I'd like to give it to you!\r\nThink of it as a gift for rescuing me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "239||||4"
msgid "What?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "240||||4"
msgid "I might be wrong about this,\r\nbut you're a Haruka-chan fan too, aren't you?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "241||||4"
msgid "You had this determined look on your face when you\r\nasked if I was a fan myself. That made it kinda obvious."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "242||||4"
msgid "Besides, it was really cool seeing you\r\nbeat the crap out of those guys."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "243||||4"
msgid "Please, take it. This picture is gonna\r\nbe happier with you, I just know it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "244||||4"
msgid "Thank you. Fandom really is a bizarre thing, huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "245||||4"
msgid "I guess you're right. Honestly, I'm just happy I got\r\nto meet someone else who likes Haruka-chan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "246||||4"
msgid "It's been getting harder and harder\r\nto support her publicly lately."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "247||||4"
msgid "Have you followed Haruka-chan since the beginning?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "248||||4"
msgid "Yeah, of course! I was even there for her\r\nfinal show at the Japan Dome a couple of years ago!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "249||||4"
msgid "The media kept calling her the yakuza's daughter,\r\nsaying she betrayed her fans by lying to us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "250||||4"
msgid "But I don't think she betrayed us at all."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "251||||4"
msgid "The courage and strength her songs gave me was real.\r\nI can't fault her for some personal issues after that."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "252||||4"
msgid "If Haruka-chan finds her way back on stage, I'll be there\r\ncheering my lungs out for her every step of the way."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "253||||4"
msgid "I'm glad to hear that. It sounds like\r\nHaruka's even luckier than she realizes."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "254||||4"
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "255||||4"
msgid "Oh, it's nothing. Thanks again."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "256||||4"
msgid "I'm the one who should be thanking you!\r\nYou really saved my skin, fellow Haruka fan!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "257||||4"
msgid "All right, I should bring this back to Ayaka.\r\nI think she's over in the Children's Park."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "258||||4"
msgid "Oh! Mister Kazuma-san!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "259||||4"
msgid "Here you go. This is your present."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "260||||4"
msgid "Wow, it's amazing! She's so pretty!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "261||||4"
msgid "Thanks a bunch, Mister!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "262||||4"
msgid "Take care of it, okay?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "263||||4"
msgid "I will! I'll treasure it forever!\r\nThis is the best!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "264||||4"
msgid "I'm gonna go home and decorate it now!\r\nBye bye, Mister! Thank you so much!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "265||||4"
msgid "Of course. Be safe on your way home, okay?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "266||||4"
msgid "Mhm!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "267||||4"
msgid "Phew, she seems thrilled with that picture.\r\nIt was definitely worth all the trouble."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "268||||4"
msgid "Oh, Mister Kazuma! I'm so glad I found you!\r\nI've been looking everywhere!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "269||||4"
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "270||||4"
msgid "Here, I made you a drawing!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "271||||4"
msgid "This is..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "272||||4"
msgid "It's me, Haruka-chan, and you, Mister Kazuma!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "273||||4"
msgid "You included me?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "274||||4"
msgid "Well, you're Haruka-chan's dad,\r\nright Mister Kazuma?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "275||||4"
msgid "How did you know...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "276||||4"
msgid "I realized it the first time you talked to me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "277||||4"
msgid "When you mentioned Haruka-chan,\r\nyour eyes lit up like only a dad's eyes would."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "278||||4"
msgid "......"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "279||||4"
msgid "I love my dad. He has the warmest,\r\nmost calmest eyes in the world."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "280||||4"
msgid "That's kinda how you looked, Mister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "281||||4"
msgid "I guess I can't hide it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "282||||4"
msgid "Anyways, Haruka-chan's just an idol to me."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "283||||4"
msgid "But it's different for you. You probably\r\nknow like, everything about her, Mister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "284||||4"
msgid "You might be right."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "285||||4"
msgid "Someday, I wanna hang out with you guys. Just me,\r\nHaruka-chan, and Mister Kazuma. That's why I drew this!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "286||||4"
msgid "It's actually pretty good. They look just like us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "287||||4"
msgid "Thanks. Um, I wish Haruka-chan could see it, too."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "288||||4"
msgid "Yeah. I was thinking the same thing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "289||||4"
msgid "You know what? I'll take it upon myself\r\nto make sure she gets it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "290||||4"
msgid "Really!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "291||||4"
msgid "I promise you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "292||||4"
msgid "Thanks so much, Mister!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "293||||4"
msgid "Oh, it's really late! My mom's gonna be\r\nsuper worried if I'm not home soon!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "294||||4"
msgid "Bye bye, Mister Kazuma.\r\nPlease show this to Haruka-chan for me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "295||||4"
msgid "Don't worry, I will."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "296||||4"
msgid "Please, No More!"
msgstr ""

